declarations.doc: X has not won. This does not hold, as X wins most of the times.
declarations.name: XHasNotWon

declarations.doc: O has not won. This should hold, as O can only achieve a draw.
declarations.name: OHasNotWon

declarations.doc:
This is not always true, as if O picks the right moves, the game will
result in a stalemate.
declarations.name: XMustEventuallyWin

declarations.doc:
It's not a stalemate if one player has won or the board is not filled
Check with `quint run --invariant=NotStalemate tictactoe.qnt`
declarations.name: NotStalemate

declarations.doc:
OHasNotWon is our default invariant for running the simulator/verifier
as it is the only invariant that holds. Check `NotStalemate` for an
interesting counterexample.
declarations.name: inv

declarations.doc: Either X or O will make a move, depending on the value of `nextTurn`
declarations.name: step

489.doc: O has not won. This should hold, as O can only achieve a draw.
489.name: OHasNotWon
